name: LoliRock
overview:
Iris’s earthling life is turned upside down when she learns that she’s actually an alien princess! When girl band LoliRock holds an audition for a third member, Iris tries out… and is suddenly surrounded by a dazzling light. Talia and Auriana have found their fellow princess, heir to the throne of Ephedia.

Years ago, when this distant crystal planet fell under the spell of the evil Gramorr, the infant Iris was sent to earth for safekeeping. But now, the people of Ephedia need freeing.

It’s a quest for which Iris is needed, and one that is done under the guise of being a pop band! It’s a battle against alien agents and crystal monsters… while appealing to crowds of adoring fans!

In the powerful second series, they are joined by two new princesses, Carissa and Lyna in their mission.

seasons.name: Season 1
seasons.overview: Iris is a teenage girl who likes to sing and help others. However, when she sings, strange events happen. Encouraged by her best friend, Iris ends up auditioning for a girl rock band, but her power destroys the room and she is later attacked by two strangers. The judges at the audition, Talia and Auriana, come to help her, and they explain to her that she is actually a princess with magical powers that must save her kingdom of Ephedia from the clutches of Gramorr who has taken over. The only way to save it is to master her powers and to find the Oracle Gems of the Royal Crown of Ephedia, which are scattered across the Earth. Over the course of the series, the three girls try to live ordinary teenage lives as rock stars of the all-girl band "LoliRock", while training Iris in secret. But when Gramoor sends Praxina and Mephisto and has them summon monsters to cause chaos, the girls must work together as magical girl warrior princesses.

episodes.name: To Find a Princess
episodes.overview: Teen Iris joins a pop music group and discovers that she and her bandmates are actually superpowered princesses from another world.

episodes.name: Sing for Me
episodes.overview: When Mephisto and Praxina steal their voices, the princesses must stop them from sending the voices to Gramorr, who wants to use them as a weapon.

episodes.name: A Promise Is a Promise
episodes.overview: The girls discover an oracle gem on display in a museum. But to get it, they must take on Mephisto, Praxina and a vicious dinosaur skeleton.

episodes.name: Flower Power
episodes.overview: Iris uses magic to grow a rose for a flower show, sparking a showdown between the princesses and Mephisto, Praxina and a giant enchanted snumple.

episodes.name: Talia and Kyle Sitting in a Tree
episodes.overview: When cute Kyle takes a shine to Talia, she rebuffs his attention. But before long, she discovers there's more to this boy than meets the eye.

episodes.name: Be Mine
episodes.overview: When Iris's magic backfires and bewitches her with a love charm, only a kiss from Nathaniel can break the spell. Has Iris found her true love?

episodes.name: Sirens
episodes.overview: While helping a boy search an underwater shipwreck for long-lost family jewels, Iris, Talia and Auriana do battle with a sea monster sent by Gramorr.

episodes.name: Xeris
episodes.overview: The princesses go after Praxina and Mephisto after they take Talia's magical medallion, an amulet that can reveal the location of her missing family.

episodes.name: Batty
episodes.overview: After Iris saves a scientist who got trapped in a cave looking for an energy-rich ore, the twins attack with a giant bat to steal the ore for Gramorr.

episodes.name: Camp Princess
episodes.overview: When the girls accompany a timid camper who wants to sleep overnight in the woods, Praxina and Mephisto attack with magic beasts from a totem pole.

episodes.name: Heavy Metal
episodes.overview: When the twins steal a boy's electric guitar, the girls race to get it back, but first they must face a monster made of noisy musical instruments.

episodes.name: The Birthday
episodes.overview: A mysterious music box gives Iris strange dreams, including the location of an oracle gem. Should she skip her aunt's birthday party to retrieve it?

episodes.name: Shanila Surprise
episodes.overview: Iris reaches the next stage of her magical training, Shanila. Her powers are soon tested when Gramorr orders a vicious attack to stop her progress.

episodes.name: Step Right Up
episodes.overview: After Praxina and Mephisto infiltrate a charity carnival at an orphanage, the princesses face an attack by a gang of enchanted stuffed animals.

episodes.name: Stitches
episodes.overview: Auriana designs outfits for Iris and Talia to model at a fashion show, but the twins turn a sewing machine into a monster to steal the magic apparel.

episodes.name: Lucky Star
episodes.overview: Performing at a lonesome movie star's house party, the princesses confront Mephisto and Praxina and help their celebrity host make some true friends.

episodes.name: Legend of Lake Agnes
episodes.overview: Praxina and Mephisto launch an underwater attack on the princesses during an outing on the lake to look for Aggie, the local legendary lake monster.

episodes.name: Spellbound
episodes.overview: The princesses race to recover a powerful spell book that they accidentally donated to a book sale, but Praxina and Mephisto are a step ahead of them.

episodes.name: The Haunting
episodes.overview: When a girl moves into a house rumored to be haunted, the princesses assure her it's not—until Mephisto and Praxina send a ghost to attack them.

episodes.name: Castles in the Sand
episodes.overview: While the princesses perform at a beach party, Mephisto and Praxina create a cleverly magic-resistant sand monster to kidnap Nathaniel.

episodes.name: Raffle Baffle
episodes.overview: When fundraising raffle tickets start to disappear, the princesses discover that Gramorr is using two powerful new minions to do his dirty work.

episodes.name: Dance Craze
episodes.overview: Just as Ephedia's most powerful sorceress arrives to teach the princesses a rare spell, Iris races off to save Missy from Praxina and Mephisto.

episodes.name: No Thanks for the Memories
episodes.overview: Mephisto and Praxina steal Iris' memory and convince her to attack Talia and Auriana. How can her friends bring Iris back from the dark side?

episodes.name: Smart
episodes.overview: Gramorr sends the twins to capture Doug and his smartphone after he takes revealing videos of everything the girls do in the course of a day.

episodes.name: Home (1)
episodes.overview: An asteroid hurtling toward Earth sends the girls back to Ephedia, where Gramorr demands that they retrieve for him the kingdom's enchanted crown.

episodes.name: Home (2)
episodes.overview: Still on Ephedia, Talia and Auriana join the resistance movement against Gramorr, who captures Iris as she tries to steal the crown to keep it safe.
